{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3364569,"name":"Emily B","username":"confused_ferret_57","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/c/b38774/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-04-17T22:14:45.887Z","cooked":"

My team is at the Championship event and just got our new radio this morning. Love the radio, but we now can’t find the IP address for our OrangePi. We run Photonvision over OrangePi for our note sensing, and it works fine, but the IP address changed so we can’t pull up photonvision to check the camera angle or tune any values. It has done this at past competitions as well, and we know it has something to do with the radio being reprogrammed. Usually, it always changed to the same IP, but it’s different this time and we don’t know how to find it.
Things we have tried:

  • testing the note sensing (works fine I just can’t pull up the camera view)
  • angry IP scanner (tried all active IPs within range from 10.TE.AM.0 to 10.TE.AM.255 and none worked)
  • OrangePi has a programmed static IP for all competitions, but still changes every competition
    Anyone have suggestions?
